The Company employs a total return investment approach for the domestic and foreign defined benefit pension plan assets. A mix
of equities and fixed income investments are used to maximize the long-term return of assets for a prudent level of risk. In
determining the expected long-term rate of return on defined benefit pension plan assets, management considers the historical rates
of return, the nature of investments and an expectation of future investment strategies. The target allocations for plan assets are
35% – 65% equity securities, 35% – 55% fixed income securities and 0% – 10% other (including alternative investments and cash).
